items.name: Barghest / Fairy Knight Gawain (Fate GO)
items.description:
LoRa used to generate images of the character Fairy Knight Gawain (also known as Barghest) from Fate/Grand Order. Comes with various outfits.

The main trigger tag used is barghest. Depending on the outfit you want, additional tags are required. These are as follows:

  • First ascension: ascension1 (optional: armor). If you keep getting the gauntlets from her second ascension, try putting black gauntlets in the negatives.

  • Second ascension: ascension2 (optional: black dress, single pauldron, pantyhose).

  • Ice warrior: ice-warrior (optional: bikini, single gauntlet). Adding white scarf isn't necessary, and adding bare shoulders can help in preventing the pauldron from her second ascension.

  • Like a lady: like-a-lady (optional: off shoulder, red sweater, choker).

  • Buster shirt: buster shirt. Surprisingly, this works pretty well on its own.

Issues:

  • Any outfit will occasionally incorporate bits of the second ascension into the armor, likely because the dataset contains so many images of her second ascension.

  • I tried incorporating ascension 3 as well, but there were too few images in my dataset to get accurate recreations. I may try including it in future versions.

If there are any other issues or suggestions on how to improve the model, please let me know!

items.name: Gurande (g-size) LoCon
items.description:
This art style model I trained had the biggest dataset by far with a total of 927 images between public ones on his Pixiv scraped from Gelbooru and paid ones from his FANBOX leaked on Kemono Party (which include explicit variants). I had to edit quite a lot of images using Lama Cleaner and delete others which deemed untrainable to me, I also edited those explicit ones having censorship with an inpaint model I used in ChaiNNer for bars and WebUI for mosaic (since DeepCreamPy and similar methods like DeepMosaic both suck ballz and are very outdated, wish we had a new model and program in order to demosaic hentai/JAV shit in general besides JAVPlayer, which would hopefully work on Linux too...). Also I included both his old and current style together since I love 'em both, so expect this model to sometimes shift randomly between both styles with each generation

Anyways, this artist right here is another favorite of mine, especially since he's HEAVLY obssessed with pantyhose as much as I do, the way he draws the fabric of them is so astounishing to me. Even the faces he draws are very adorable and he adapts the usage of 3D for his backgrounds which he then traces over lightly, although it may not always generate them in 3D all the time, as it mostly generates simplified 2D ones with not much detail due to the dataset I suppose. But it does one hell of a job at nailing his distinct pantyhose shading very well which I'm thankful of, although this doesn't mean you should ALWAYS generate females wearing pantyhose like he always draws them wearing those on, it also applies it to other kinds of legwears as well such as thighhighs, kneehighs and leggings too I guess (or you could just generate 'em bare legged for all I care, just don't post your generations with this or other style models of mine on Pixiv, since I read that they don't allow images imitating other artists anymore).

items.name: DarkestDungeon
items.description:
v2.1 Updated 19/5/23

If you enjoy the models I create, please consider buying me a coffee!

Ko-fi

I am pleased to announce the release of DarkestDungeon v2 (lora)

What is it?

DarkestDungeon is lora revolving around the artstyle from 'Darkest Dungeon', one of my favourite games of all time. Applies a style to whatever you want, portraits to landscapes. It does it all.

It has been trained partly with modders/game devs in mind. Because of this, you can now make images with a plain white background, such as characters, items, weapons and armour and anything you can think of. (See trigger words below, but it works for ddstyle too).

How do I use it?

To recreate it's atmospheric artstyle, there are a couple of simple rules that I recommend following:

1- The trigger word "ddstyle" goes at the front of your prompt.

2- Keep negatives simple. I use "(worst quality, low quality, normal quality:1.4)"

3- Try adding "darkest dungeon"

4- Play around with the Lora strength if you are finding it hard to get what you want, and try to remove conflicting keywords.

5- Use booru tags as this was trained on a NAI based model: https://danbooru.donmai.us/tags

What models are best?

- It's intended to work with any anime model. Realistic models aren't as effective


Trigger words:

"ddstyle"

"ddtrinketicon"

"crimson court"

"the Cove"

"the Weald"

"the Warrens"

"the Ruins"

Some have been removed, but I'll add them back in soon.

items.name: Angel Dust (Hazbin Hotel)
items.description:
My first LoHA/LoRA.

You need the stable diffusion LyCORIS extension in order to make this work. Otherwise you'll get an error about the LoRA layer being named wrong or something along those lines.

Base model is NAI, trained on 228 solo images of angel dust. Works fairly well on the higher end of values (0.6-1.0). 10 epochs, 3 repetitions. 2280 steps in total.

I recommend using this LoHA on a model that's good at generating furry features, such as fluffy-rock, crosskemono, or a merge between the two.

Used a combination of the LyCORIS Experiments and "How to make a LoRA" guide on Civit to figure out how to make it.

I hope you'll enjoy it!

Mai Mizuhashi (aka MARiA) is the singer of Garnidelia, a J-pop duo. She's also a model, dancer and costume designer.

1200-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images (most of them provided by @Wiggyfreak1) with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (marigarn:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, knitted sweater, choker, hair updo, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

items.name: Dave McKean Style
items.description:
Dave McKean is a British artist, illustrator, and filmmaker known for his distinct and innovative approach to visual storytelling. He has made significant contributions to the fields of graphic novels, illustration, and film.

McKean's style is highly versatile and experimental, combining various mediums and techniques to create striking and atmospheric artwork. He often blends photography, painting, collage, and digital manipulation to create unique and layered compositions.

His illustrations and artwork are often characterized by a surreal and dreamlike quality, featuring elements of fantasy, mythology, and the subconscious. McKean's ability to seamlessly integrate different artistic disciplines results in visually stunning and thought-provoking imagery.

He is particularly renowned for his collaborations with writer Neil Gaiman, most notably on the critically acclaimed graphic novel "The Sandman" series. McKean's distinct visual style played a pivotal role in shaping the overall tone and atmosphere of the series, helping to establish it as a landmark work in the world of comic books.

In addition to his work in graphic novels and illustration, McKean has also directed and produced several short films and feature films. His films often incorporate a blend of live-action and animation, further showcasing his talent for storytelling through visual mediums.

Dave McKean's art challenges conventional storytelling methods and pushes the boundaries of visual narrative. His innovative approach, combined with his technical mastery and distinct style, has made him a highly influential figure in the realms of graphic novels, illustration, and film. His work continues to inspire and captivate audiences with its depth, complexity, and evocative imagery.

items.name: Bonk
items.description:
If you want a more traditional lora experience i recommend the 576 version of the lora.

This is a model trained on bonk's style and most of bonk's esix portfolio of imagery. This model is intended to be used with fluffyrock derivative models such as Omega mix, which can be found in my user profile. This lora works best when combined with other artists to give visual structure to the image, such is the weakness/strength of style selective models such as fluffyrock.

Note that i have added the term "eyeliner" to associate the heavy colored eyelashes of bonk's style. you may need to use "eyeliner eyelashes" inorder to get them to really pop

I might do a training on nai at some point.

Remember that my representational images are non exhaustive and that creativity is the onus of the user of the lora.

Enjoy.
